Title: Zoolander 2 Trailer (2016) - Paramount Pictures
Comment:
It's got some good laughs. Lots of random Western cultural references.  Fantastic cameos.  You can see his nod to his father - Stiller Sr. - a lot of  vaudeville banter between Owen Wilson and Jr.   There is some odd  "Bro-Love".  It's got slapstick and sex.  You can tell their targeted demographic.    A BIG "thumbs down"  though,  for all the female roles being pretty much superfluous T & A.  What year is this? Not that any of the characters where that fleshed out, but dang.  And the only Black male character is  totally feminized.  No possibility of romantic competition?  Huh?  That's sad. Pobrecitos.   It also seems weird that the only male with an "African / Black" sounding name is a harlequin with  white "Afro-Puffs".  lol    But I have to say they are 'equal opportunity',   over the top   writers.  Some of it felt a tinge homophobic.   Even though they brought in  a funny "Steve" reference.   It felt like a gimmick.   Who knows?  Maybe not.   But they sure know how to put their fingers into everybody's culture, wrap it up and sell it.  The Pop culture. Black culture.  And the Youth culture.  The Gay culture.   At the same time making some laughs while they give a big F-you TO US culture as a whole.    

2 1/2 - 3 stars

Title: Zoolander 2 Trailer (2016) - Paramount Pictures
Comment:
ok, people. the only reason the trans character is offensive, is that they are played by a cis gender man! that is it. 
People who think it's making fun of trans people, no, it's making fun of the other guys. i forgot their names. 
they are "the biggest supermodel in the whole world". they are successful. yes, this could turn offensive but so far IT IS NOT. it is no more offensive to trans people than it is to models or anyone else who is made fun of. it's not personal. 

and people being rude about the trans people sticking up for themselves in the media, just stop. yes, we can be over-sensitive but it because we are sick of being unfairly represented. i get that they probably will not be poked fun of any more than any other character but the result of this is that some people may think it is okay to do so. it may make people assume that it is ok to ask about what is in a trans persons pants when it is none of their business.

Yes, we take these things too seriously but when almost half of us attempt suicide at some point and almost all are harassed at some point or don't feel safe and then there is negative things in the media, possibly like this, can you blame us for not supporting it. We, as a community, only want to be accepted. 

things like this, where they are treated like just another character might be the start of us being accepted, they could also just fuel the hate about us. 

but seriously, they should have used a non-binary or gender fluid actor. i get they used cumberbatch because they will hit another demographic and get more money which is the entire reason because why else would they be making a second film when it's not needed.

Comment:
Oh look its a bunch of actors playing the exact same role they've played their entire careers. 

All of this stuff was funny 15 years ago, when it was original and fresh. This kind of dumb as dumb can get humor should've died out long ago. This is a comedy, and I did nothing but cringe the entire trailer. And Fucking Will Ferrell, does his acting chops extend to yelling stupid lines that aren't funny? And thats it? I mean fuck me, when are they going to stop pouring money into these kind of movies. 

Adam Sander, Ben Stiller, Owen Wilson, Kirsten Wigg, Will Ferrell and Kevin Hart (just to name a few), all they do is the same fucking thing. For their entire career, and it stopped being any good about 2007. Probably before that.

Vince Vaughan, Matt mcconaughey, Woody Harrelson at least took chances in their careers and tried serious dramatic acting. True Detective season 2 was a big MEH, but Vaughans performance was believable. 

I just struggle to respect actors that do the same thing over and over. Don't they want to look back on their career and know they got the most out of it? They all just mail it in movie after movie, happy to pump out totally forgettable crap.

Title: Zoolander 2 Trailer (2016) - Paramount Pictures
Comment:
To those of you who have come to this video to spew condemning speech about this trailer's "blatant transphobia", a couple of things to think about:

1) It is a 10 second clip. Within that clip, Cumberbatch had TWO lines. Did his character state their gender? Did they say they were trans? Non-binary? Is there any official article out there stating that the character All is explicitly "not cis"? It's becoming apparent that today any display of gender nonconformity is to be met with the "YOU MUST BE TRANS" rhetoric. It's ridiculous and harmful.

2) The whole Zoolander franchise is one of comedy-- of satire. The ignorant comments made by Wilson's and Stiller's characters to All was clearly meant mockingly (not in the universe of the movie-- to the audience of the movie). All's response was only fitting to those inappropriate, invasive questions. Cumberbatch's character responded in a proper way-- not even giving those questions any attention. 

Fine, boycott the movie all you want. But do so because it looks like a shitty movie. Not because of the liberal media pressing this "you must be so offended because we say so though we don't have any evidence or argument to back it up" agenda.

Please, do yourself a favor and think for yourself. Stop this culture of bandwagoning. Teenagers of today, be. your. own. person.
